      • assignUniqueHash

        public void assignUniqueHash()
        Set the unique hash on this Target. This must be called before any Target is persisted to the database, since this is used to lookup Targets/TargetAssociations for a given target.

      • createUniqueHash

        Returns:

      • getUniqueName

        public java.lang.String getUniqueName()
        Return the name that can uniquely identify this Target within a TargetSource/Application. This is used as the "target" of a Permission when the converting these to Permission objects, and is also stored as the name of the IdentityEntitlement.

      • createUniqueName

        public static java.lang.String createUniqueName(java.lang.String name,
                                                java.lang.String fullPath,
                                                java.lang.String targetHost)
        Create a name that can uniquely identify a Target within a TargetSource/Application.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the Target.
        fullPath - The fullPath of the Target - possibly null.
        targetHost - The targetHost of the Target - possibly null.
        Returns:
        A name that can uniquely identify a Target within a TargetSource/Application.
